Not sure how it works in New York, but in California if you call 911 from a cellphone it goes straight to CHP. CHP then requires the incident address in order to forward the call to the proper agency the incident address is policed by. The only way to circumvent this is if you know/search the agencies dedicated 911 phone number, which is not the same as dialing 911. So if the friend in New York truly called 911 it would have gone to whatever agency in New York that is the domain for 911, they would've had to figure out which agency is over where the incident took place and forward from there causing a huge delay in time which is crucial in DV cases. So I'm sorry, but I don't believe the friend in New York was the one who called 911, I believe it was the one staying in the other penthouse, which makes more sense.
